Question: How would you invite your friends to a party if phones and the Internet did not exist?
Answer:
If my friends were in walking distance I would go to their houses and ask each one of my fruends if they would like to attend a party I am hosting. Also if there were friends that I would like to invite that live far from my house I would write them invite letters and correspond with them via the U.S. postal services or in other words by mail. 